(thirdQuint)Feasibility Study: Evaluation of the Treatment of Striae Using Ultherapy in Combination With Laser Treatment.

 This is a prospective, randomized, single-blinded, pilot clinical trial to evaluate the use of the Ulthera(R) System in combination with the 70W Alma Pixel CO2 laser for efficacious results in the treatment of abdominal striae rubra and striae alba.

 Subjects will be randomized to one of three treatment groups.

 Study personnel conducting efficacy measures will be blinded to the assigned treatment groups.

 Changes from baseline in overall skin texture and appearance of abdominal striae will be assessed at study follow-up visits.

 2D images, 3D images and patient satisfaction questionnaires will be obtained.

